<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>Armed police swooped on a man in fancy dress spotted carrying a samurai sword which turned out to be a novelty umbrella.</p>

<p>Officers armed with Tasers dashed to the street in Leamington Spa, Warwickshire, after receiving reports of a 'machete man' prowling the town centre.</p>

<p>But they were stunned when the man turned out to be wearing a fancy dress costume with an umbrella which had a 'sword hilt' handle.</p>

<p>Warwickshire Police tweeted a snap, above, of the man wearing Cosplay and a mask posing by a patrol car after the bizarre incident on a street in Leamington Spa on Tuesday</p>

<p>He was wearing a kilt and sinister laughing clown face mask as part of a Cosplay outfit - short for costume play.</p>

<p>Cosplay fans dress up as a character often from popular anime or computer games. </p>

<p>Warwickshire Police tweeted a snap of the man posing by a patrol car after the bizarre incident on Tuesday, and said: 'Not everything is always as it seems.</p>

<p>'Patrol officers from Leamington Spa deployed with Taser to reports of a man walking down Warwick Street holding a samurai sword.</p>

<p>'Upon engagement, the 'sword' was found to be an umbrella with a sword-hilt handle.</p>

<p>'Not everything is always as it seems. Cosplay safe!' </p>
